text: I read about it and it made perfect sense. I read seriously hundreds of testimonials and success stories, before and afters, anything I could read! Reversing heart disease, diabetes, lowering cholesterol, so many things! I lost my mom in January due to heart disease. Talked to her that morning, joking and laughing, planning my sons first birthday, ended the phone call with our 'love you more.' She went into cardiac arrest that afternoon while riding in the car. She was on life support for a few days before we took her off. She survived 24 hours on her own before dying. All because she didn't take care of herself. I have birth to my second son 6 days after she died, 3 weeks early. 2 months later, in March, my dad had a double bypass and valve replacement. He suffered a stroke after surgery that went unnoticed for 2 weeks. How can I continue to eat the way they did and be happy?? I almost lost my dad after losing mom. I have 2 boys to take care of and I don't want them to lose me prematurely. Not to mention, I feel amazing. I struggle every day to eat right but when I do, I feel amazing with so much energy. I'll never revert back to my eating habits. (created at:2012-10-16 17:24:33)

text: I started Crossfit and instantly saw results within a few months. When my coaches were impressed with my improvement they were surprised that I was doing my wods so well without eating paleo. I spoke to my trainer and he gave me guidelines how to get started. After a week of eating paleo I noticed a huge difference in my workouts and ever since I started it my progress in strength and everything else is unbelievable. I'm a small girl 5ft 115lbs and since I started paleo my lifts have increased dramatically . I am physically and mentally stronger than ever. My deadlift from when I started Crossfit (and eating like crap) was under 100lbs and now I'm proud to stay my 1rm for my dl is 215 ! 100 lbs over my weight. Paleo has helped me achieve so much more than I ever imagined and I got many friends and my boyfriend into it and happy to see I'm changing people's lives and diets in a positive way! text: Became a diagnosed celiac after 7years of misdiagnosing and hell. I found out about glutenfree the hard way. Worked for years in this field and advocacy to know deep in my heart I was still not all better on the Gf diet alone. I interviewed several authors and doctors on radio shows and on the Internet discussing the diet and came across the Paleo diet. It sure made sense! I gave it a try and within days ALL my symptoms dissipated. I felt I was on to something. I tried it for 3 months and started speaking broadly on shows about it to help others!!! I started getting emails and letters from other people and celiacs in the same situation who decided to give the Paleo a try. Later hearing back from many of them saying it too (Paleo) had changed their lives. I realize it's a big change in how one eats but it makes so much sense and truly increases ones quality if life. I feel it truly saved my life. 2 of my three kids are celiacs and they too tried Paleo and never went back. Their odd symptoms have gone as well Paleo is mans natural diet and it's great! I will continue to speak broadly about Paleo and help people feel better. I feel great now! (created at:2012-10-16 17:37:56)
label: non-cyberbullying

text: @paleobakehouse I went paleo by accident!! lol my gym told me about it but they didn't say it was paleo-they just told me to try to stop eating bread, rice, pasta! I was shocked and thought I couldn't do it but little by little I did and found myself feeling better and losing weight! I started crossfit January 2011 and started paleo slowly but got strict in June 2011 and found I could do it everyday! I started researching recipes in different paleo websites and have won 2 Paleo challenges at my gym! I'm down 75lbs within a year and 10 months and I feel great! this is a lifestyle change for me and I'm happy and blessed I came across a community of people to lead me to the right path! ____ (created at:2012-10-16 17:38:34)

text: At the beginning of this year, I was sick sick sick. Waking up and vomiting about once a week, lethargic, bruising all over, skin problems etc etc. my life was just a mess. I stopped working out, I hated my job, I lost my drive and motivation, I was depressed and I needed a change! I began to cut certain things out (mainly grains) and the vomiting stopped. Once I started feeling better, I began to cut more things out and began working out again! I started slow with cutting dairy out, then started reading about the paleo lifestyle! I read about the side effects that certain foods could have on our body and realized I was struggling with nearly all of those same issues! I decided to go paleo for a month and it completely changed my life. I found I could workout harder and still eat a lot of great food! It was unlike any other diet I had ever been on! My migraines stopped, my acne cleared up, even my horrendous allergies subsided!! It was just amazing. I now lead a mostly paleo lifestyle but indulge every once in a while on a dairy treat. I can totally see a difference, immediately when I eat something non-paleo! It has truly changed my life! (created at:2012-10-16 20:05:11)

text: I got diagnosed with stage 2b uterine cancer in February. Luckily I had an oncologist who recommended a diet low in sugar and high in protein to help combat it in the most natural way.
